In its fourth game of the season, Michigan defeated the [[Indiana Hoosiers football|Indiana Hoosiers]] 37 to 0.  Michigan posted four second quarter touchdowns, and Indiana only got close to the Michigan end zone once in the first quarter.<ref name=CFMPSSa9AIHNC>{{cite web|url=http://www.nytimes.com/1997/10/05/sports/college-football-midwest-penn-state-streak-at-9-as-illini-have-no-clue.html|title=College Football: Midwest; Penn State Streak at 9 As Illini Have No Clue|accessdate=2010-07-24|date=1997-10-05|work=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref>  The win was the eighth consecutive and 23rd of 24 for Michigan over Indiana.  It was Michigan's first shutout since November 11, 1995, against {{cfb link|year=1995|team=Purdue Boilermakers|title=Purdue}}.<ref name=MvI/>  The game pitted Michigan against former Michigan assistant coach and first year head coach [[Cam Cameron]].<ref name=MvI/>  

Brian Griese passed for 204 yards and a touchdown, before giving way to Tom Brady after one series in the third quarter.<ref name=CFMPSSa9AIHNC/>  Baker kicked three field goals and four extra points.<ref name=MvI/>  Howard led Michigan receivers with 65&nbsp;yards on 7 catches, and Anthony Thomas led the rushers with 65 yards on 14 carries.<ref name=MvI/>  Charles Woodson had a 21-yard reception.<ref name=MvI/>  The Michigan defense held Indiana to negative 2 return yards and 16 rushing yards on 27 carries.<ref name=MvI/>

In the first quarter, Baker's 27-yard field goal was the only scoring.  Twenty-nine seconds into the second quarter, Howard's 3-yard run gave Michigan a 10&ndash;0 lead.<ref name=MvI/>  Later in the quarter, Michigan scored three touchdowns in a 5:54 span.  First, Griese connected with Streets for 18 yards.  Thomas and Patrick McCall added 14-yard and 3-yard scoring runs to give Michigan a 31&ndash;0 lead with 1:59 remaining in the first half.<ref name=MvI/>  Baker added 35-yard and 40-yard field goals in the third quarter to complete the scoring.<ref name=MvI/>
{{clear}}

====Week 5: Northwestern====
{{AFB game box start
| Title = '''Week 5: Northwestern at (6) Michigan'''<ref name=NvM>{{cite web|url=http://www.usatoday.com/sports/scores97/97284/97284338.htm|title=Northwestern vs. Michigan|accessdate=2010-07-21|date=1997-10-11|work=[[USA Today]]}}</ref>
| Visitor = {{cfb link|year=1997|team=Northwestern Wildcats|title=Northwestern}} (2&ndash;5, 0&ndash;3)
| Host = Michigan (5&ndash;0, 2&ndash;0)
| V1 = 3| V2 =0| V3 =3| V4 =0
| H1 = 0| H2 =13| H3 =0| H4 =10
| Date = Saturday, October 11, 1997
| Location = [[Michigan Stadium]]<br /> {{USCity|Ann Arbor|Michigan}}
| StartTime = 
| ElapsedTime = 
| Attendance = 106,048
| Weather = 
| Referee = 
