A total of 31 members of the 1997 Michigan Wolverines team played in the NFL.  A 32nd player, [[Rob Renes]] was drafted by the [[Indianapolis Colts]] but suffered a career-ending fracture of the [[Lumbar vertebrae|L-5 vertebrae]] two weeks into [[National Football League Training Camp|training camp]] with the Colts in 2000.  A 33rd player, [[Russell Shaw]], played seven years in the [[Arena Football League (1987<U+2013>2008)|Arena Football League]].  The 31 team members who played in the NFL are:  
